WorkItem.Description: When loading up the Prot Paladin model, items are not displayed on the right. I've tried resetting all the item caches with no luck. This seems to only be the case with Prot, as Holy and Ret load items when switching to their models.

Comments.Message: I am having the same Issue.

Why was this rated as a low impact.  This is a huge deal, there is no gear available to any prot pallies.  Yes it's only one portion of the user group, but Rawr is basically borked for that entire group of people.

Because MOST models don't work right now and everything model-specific almost always gets rated as Low Impact. Medium and High Impact tickets are usually things that affect every user, regardless of model

Shouldn't the status of the model not be Cata:Mostly then?  If you can't use the model to add any gear, I would think that would be less than mostly finished.  I could be wrong, and I really appreciate the work you guys do, I just think the model status may be misleading.  

Thanks for explaining that all model issues are rated as low impact.

a HA!

No Gemming Templates have been set by default to On. If you open Edit Gemming Templates in ProtPaladin and turn on a set of them, your items will show up.
Thank you, that does in deed fix it.  :)

Thanks for finding that one, I just didn't switch the default gemming template from epic to rare.

ProtPaladin has a ways to go, a lot of the calculations are wrong and the scales are off-kilter.  I'm working on fixing these, but only have time on the weekends to do so right now.
